    <!-- TOP CARE PRACTICES -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sec-head center fade-up">
          <span class="label">The Fundamentals</span>
          <h2 class="sec-title">Three Habits That <em>Preserve Scent</em></h2>
          <p class="sec-sub">Get these right and your collection will smell exactly as intended, bottle after bottle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="usp-grid fade-up">
          <div class="usp-card">
            <div class="usp-ic"><span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">inventory_2</span></div>
            <h3>The Right Environment</h3>
            <p>Store fragrances in a cool, dry, dark place — a drawer, cupboard or original box. Steady conditions preserve the delicate balance of notes far better than a bright vanity shelf.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="usp-card">
            <div class="usp-ic"><span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">wb_shade</span></div>
            <h3>Avoid Light &amp; Heat</h3>
            <p>UV light and temperature swings break down fragrance compounds and dull the colour. Keep bottles away from windows, radiators and — critically in the UAE — never leave them in a hot car.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="usp-card">
            <div class="usp-ic"><span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">pan_tool</span></div>
            <h3>Careful Handling</h3>
            <p>Keep the cap on when not in use to limit air exposure, avoid shaking the bottle, and hold it by the base rather than the atomiser to protect the pump.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW TO STORE (STEPS) -->
    <section class="section alt">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sec-head center fade-up">
          <span class="label">Step by Step</span>
          <h2 class="sec-title">How to Store Your <em>Perfume</em></h2>
          <p class="sec-sub">Placement, container, temperature and light — the four levers that decide how long a fragrance lasts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="how-grid fade-up">
          <div class="how-step">
            <span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">place</span>
            <h3>Choose the Spot</h3>
            <p>An interior drawer or wardrobe shelf, away from bathrooms where humidity and heat spike, is the ideal home for your collection.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="how-step">
            <span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">inventory_2</span>
            <h3>Keep the Container Sealed</h3>
            <p>Retain the original box and always replace the cap. Both limit oxygen and light — the two forces that age a fragrance fastest.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="how-step">
            <span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">device_thermostat</span>
            <h3>Control the Temperature</h3>
            <p>Aim for a stable 15–20°C. Air-conditioned interior rooms are perfect; avoid anywhere that swings between hot and cold.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="how-step">
            <span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">wb_shade</span>
            <h3>Block the Light</h3>
            <p>Direct sunlight is a perfume's fastest route to spoilage. Dark storage keeps both the scent and the liquid's colour intact.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CLEANING & MAINTAINING -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="feature-article fade-up">
          <div class="fa-media"><img src="{{ 'cat-luxury.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Luxury perfume bottle and atomiser" /></div>
          <div class="fa-body">
            <span class="bl-cat">Maintenance</span>
            <h2>Cleaning &amp; Maintaining Bottles &amp; Atomisers</h2>
            <p>A well-kept bottle sprays evenly and looks as good as the scent inside. Wipe the exterior and nozzle with a soft, dry cloth to prevent residue build-up, and if an atomiser clogs, rinse the spray cap in warm water and let it dry fully before refitting. For travel atomisers, clean between refills so a new fragrance never mixes with the last.</p>
            <p>Treat the pump gently — most spray failures come from forcing a sticky nozzle rather than a genuine fault.</p>
            <a class="btn-ghost" href="/pages/scent-education">More scent tips <span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">arrow_forward</span></a>
          </div>
